<div id="review_900357037" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/900357037" />
    <a title="Michael Pang" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/22904145-michael-pang"><img alt="Michael Pang" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1375895620p2/22904145.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/900357037?book_show_action=true">Apr 03, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Michael Pang" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Michael Pang" href="/user/show/22904145-michael-pang">Michael Pang</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer900357037" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11014273340733068876">I came into this book a little forewarned by the good readers here at Goodreads: &quot;that this book is a SLOW buildup&quot;. <br/><br/>0-20%, slow. 20-30%, something could happen, are we leaving yet? 30-35%, is this it? No, false start. 35-45% OK, we left the castle, something has to happen right? 45%-end: Bam! Fires, dragons, magic swords, trolls, elves, demons, mountains, crossing the map, wolves (good and bad), bad dreams/good dreams, death, sieges, magical storms, ships.......<br/><br/>The slow build-up eventually drop</span>
  <span id="freeText11014273340733068876" style="display:none">I came into this book a little forewarned by the good readers here at Goodreads: "that this book is a SLOW buildup". <br /><br />0-20%, slow. 20-30%, something could happen, are we leaving yet? 30-35%, is this it? No, false start. 35-45% OK, we left the castle, something has to happen right? 45%-end: Bam! Fires, dragons, magic swords, trolls, elves, demons, mountains, crossing the map, wolves (good and bad), bad dreams/good dreams, death, sieges, magical storms, ships.......<br /><br />The slow build-up eventually drops you off the cliff into a sea of epic fantasy and it is worth it. Looking forward to picking up where the 1st book left off and would recommend this book with the warning: it is indeed a slow build-up to what ultimately looks to be some good epic fantasy.</span>
  <a data-text-id="11014273340733068876" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


