<div id="review_2005123653" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2005123653" />
    <a title="Scott  Hitchcock" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/50894754-scott-hitchcock"><img alt="Scott  Hitchcock" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1459187975p2/50894754.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2005123653?book_show_action=true">May 28, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Scott  Hitchcock" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Scott  Hitchcock" href="/user/show/50894754-scott-hitchcock">Scott  Hitchcock</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Audible Audio " href="/book/show/29372311-the-dragonbone-chair">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/50894754-scott-hitchcock?shelf=epic-fantasy">epic-fantasy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/50894754-scott-hitchcock?shelf=abandoned-series">abandoned-series</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2005123653" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3699904964481911394">2.5*<br/><br/>The writing style is very good. However the pacing is super slow. If you&apos;re going to have a slow pace, for me, you have to balance it with some sort of engaging psychological gauging of the characters usually with a high dose of empathy or some type of theoretical discussion which is thought provoking or some witty character banter. <br/><br/>I think if you like old school fantasy and it&apos;s pacing you&apos;ll love this. If you don&apos;t then not so much. </span>
  <span id="freeText3699904964481911394" style="display:none">2.5*<br /><br />The writing style is very good. However the pacing is super slow. If you're going to have a slow pace, for me, you have to balance it with some sort of engaging psychological gauging of the characters usually with a high dose of empathy or some type of theoretical discussion which is thought provoking or some witty character banter. <br /><br />I think if you like old school fantasy and it's pacing you'll love this. If you don't then not so much. </span>
  <a data-text-id="3699904964481911394" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


