<div id="review_3996298182" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3996298182" />
    <a title="Allison Hurd" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/14495279-allison-hurd"><img alt="Allison Hurd" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1530670583p2/14495279.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3996298182?book_show_action=true">Jun 10, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Allison Hurd" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Allison Hurd" href="/user/show/14495279-allison-hurd">Allison Hurd</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/14495279-allison-hurd?shelf=fantasy">fantasy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/14495279-allison-hurd?shelf=man-author">man-author</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/14495279-allison-hurd?shelf=sff-bookshelf">sff-bookshelf</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/14495279-allison-hurd?shelf=sff-2021-challenge">sff-2021-challenge</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3996298182" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1331741717682245202">Don&apos;t read this if you&apos;re planning to read with SFFBC and want no outside influence!<br/><br/><a class='jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction'>(view spoiler)</a><span class='spoilerContainer' style='display: none'>[<br/><br/>This book started with 2 strikes for me: one, the Tad Williams author page on GR is...atrocious. I&apos;m sure some overhyped agent&apos;s assistant wrote it or something but it&apos;s very offputting. I know, I know, it&apos;s not nice of me, but I&apos;m trying to explain I was personally biased so I&apos;d say you should take this with a grain of salt, but I&apos;m planning to be plenty salty so just collect whatever amount you t</span></span>
  <span id="freeText1331741717682245202" style="display:none">Don't read this if you're planning to read with SFFBC and want no outside influence!<br /><br /><a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[<br /><br />This book started with 2 strikes for me: one, the Tad Williams author page on GR is...atrocious. I'm sure some overhyped agent's assistant wrote it or something but it's very offputting. I know, I know, it's not nice of me, but I'm trying to explain I was personally biased so I'd say you should take this with a grain of salt, but I'm planning to be plenty salty so just collect whatever amount you think is appropriate.<br /><br />The other strike is that within the first 20 pages, it's a preface about how great the book is, an admonishment not to read with any assumptions, and then a bunch of fantasy words and religions that are just extremely thin veneers on European things which is a pet peeve.<br /><br />So I wasn't expecting to be thrilled, and I fulfilled that prophecy.<br /><br />On top of that:<br /><br />-Simon is a gawky, immature (in the sense that he doesn't read like a 15 year old) whiny dude who is quite uninteresting for the majority of the story, often passing out a la Bilbo at the Battle of 5 Armies.<br /><br />-The passing out didn't save us from the fight scenes! So. Many. Battles. <br /><br />-The story didn't actually START for 200 pages. And then it came in starts and fits afterwards. I think this could have been a fine entry into epic fantasy if it was 300 pages shorter.<br /><br />-Exposition galore. Oh my stars! You need a fucking diploma in Erkynland history to get anything out of this book, apparently! Who's got time for that??<br /><br />-No thought for plot? I don't understand why any of this is happening. Dude's like "I don't want to be king!" and the king is like "usurper! I'll kill you!" and everyone is just like "yeah, all right." What? Same with all the actions everyone seems to make. Why did you do that? *GIANT SHRUG* and then we move on. Especially Vorzevhna (sp). Her entrance is when I started speed reading. Super cringey women and men-gazing-at-women stuff going on here.<br /><br />-No ending! It's like Two Towers into Return of the King. It just stops mid field. But unlike Two Towers, It's substantially longer, and they go substantially shorter distances.<br /><br />I'm giving it a second star because I started skimming a lot towards the halfway part and I'll assume that made it hard for me to make the connections I'm sure others made.<br /><br />Just not for me, another mediocre entry into bloated epic fantasy with even less new content than most quest stories. Thanks, no thanks!<br /><br /> <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span><br /><br /></span>
